<div><h3>SOC 130 - Genocide </h3>  <hr>Provides students with a comparative perspective that highlights theory and concrete examples of genocide.  After surveying legal and social scientific definitions of genocide, we explore four cases of genocide that took place over the course of centuries and across several continents. The course ends with discussion of the prevention of genocide.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every year<br><br></div>		</td>
